00:00:02,415 --> 00:00:04,939
Thought today we'd one of
these almighty black canvases.

3
00:00:04,939 --> 00:00:08,031
It's time we got into doing
something on a black canvas.

4
00:00:08,031 --> 00:00:09,338
I'd like to show you how

5
00:00:09,337 --> 00:00:11,199
you can do a beautiful,
beautiful landscape

6
00:00:11,199 --> 00:00:12,764
on a black canvas.

7
00:00:12,765 --> 00:00:14,182
I've already went ahead,

8
00:00:14,182 --> 00:00:17,480
because we are short of time on this show,

9
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,688
I've already went ahead and
covered the whole canvas

10
00:00:19,687 --> 00:00:21,949
with Alizarin crimson.

11
00:00:21,949 --> 00:00:24,759
Now I'm gonna take a little Van Dyke brown

12
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:28,091
and work into the edges,
just around the edges,

13
00:00:28,091 --> 00:00:30,902
so it's, we already have it
covered with Alizarin crimson,

14
00:00:30,902 --> 00:00:33,578
and now we're putting
a little brown on it.

15
00:00:33,578 --> 00:00:37,212
The whole canvas was covered with crimson.

16
00:00:37,212 --> 00:00:38,060
There we go.

17
00:00:38,060 --> 00:00:40,060
Just around the corners.

18
00:00:41,305 --> 00:00:45,059
Thought today we'd do a
beautiful little sunset.

19
00:00:45,060 --> 00:00:46,597
And maybe we'll have a little sunset

20
00:00:46,597 --> 00:00:50,966
like the sun's going down
behind the hill back there.

21
00:00:50,966 --> 00:00:54,274
And we just have a
beautiful glow in the sky,

22
00:00:54,274 --> 00:00:56,985
and then we'll go from there.

23
00:00:56,985 --> 00:00:59,198
Now I'm gonna take and
pull this back and forth

24
00:00:59,198 --> 00:01:01,016
to a get a nice even
distribution of paint,

25
00:01:01,017 --> 00:01:04,507
working it up and down, back and forth.

26
00:01:04,507 --> 00:01:05,507
There we go.

27
00:01:10,084 --> 00:01:10,917
All right.

28
00:01:14,447 --> 00:01:17,481
Mm 'kay, now we'll start
with a one-inch brush,

29
00:01:17,481 --> 00:01:19,984
we'll use a little bit of cad yellow.

30
00:01:19,984 --> 00:01:22,549
Figure out where the
sun is, just went down,

31
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:25,439
and we're gonna start like right here.

32
00:01:25,439 --> 00:01:28,356
And begin working this paint around.

33
00:01:28,356 --> 00:01:30,227
You start in the center and work

34
00:01:30,227 --> 00:01:32,762
around and around and around,

35
00:01:32,762 --> 00:01:34,751
and already it's picking
up the Alizarin crimson

36
00:01:34,751 --> 00:01:35,751
and it's turning into

37
00:01:35,751 --> 00:01:39,918
a beautiful little yellow-ish
orange-ish glow here.

38
00:01:41,153 --> 00:01:42,153
There we go.

39
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:49,355
And we'll start right
here, let it work outward.

40
00:01:51,162 --> 00:01:53,814
You want it to get darker and
darker and darker and darker

41
00:01:53,813 --> 00:01:55,622
as it goes out toward the edges.

42
00:01:55,623 --> 00:01:59,790
So we always start with a
color in here and work outward.

43
00:02:02,099 --> 00:02:03,099
There we go.

44
00:02:10,002 --> 00:02:11,382
Okay.

45
00:02:11,383 --> 00:02:14,423
A little bit of color here, work it out,

46
00:02:14,423 --> 00:02:16,774
and I'm doing this in
little-bitty X patterns.

47
00:02:16,774 --> 00:02:20,441
Back and forth, back
and forth, there we go.

48
00:02:23,342 --> 00:02:24,175
Mm 'kay.

49
00:02:25,616 --> 00:02:27,437
Now let's take the big brush,

50
00:02:27,437 --> 00:02:29,987
and gently gently hypnotize this.

51
00:02:29,986 --> 00:02:32,819
We're still making the little X's.

52
00:02:39,449 --> 00:02:40,282
There.

53
00:02:41,651 --> 00:02:43,151
Just work that in.

54
00:02:48,538 --> 00:02:52,705
And then just enough to
take out the brushstrokes.

55
00:02:55,265 --> 00:02:56,352
Okay.

56
00:02:56,353 --> 00:02:59,103
(water sloshing)

57
00:03:01,897 --> 00:03:04,264
(paintbrush rattling)

58
00:03:04,264 --> 00:03:07,426
Okay, let's take a little bit
of Alizarin, a little brown,

59
00:03:07,426 --> 00:03:11,210
put it together here on the
brush, mix on the brush.

60
00:03:11,211 --> 00:03:12,419
And maybe back here in the distance

61
00:03:12,419 --> 00:03:14,757
we'll have a little foothill back here.

62
00:03:14,757 --> 00:03:18,257
Just let this brush bounce along and play.

63
00:03:19,472 --> 00:03:20,472
There we go.

64
00:03:23,056 --> 00:03:24,942
Don't let the size of
this big brush scare you.

65
00:03:24,942 --> 00:03:27,025
It does fantastic things.

66
00:03:31,634 --> 00:03:32,467
Okay.

67
00:03:34,915 --> 00:03:38,082
Now, maybe we'll have some highlights.

68
00:03:40,655 --> 00:03:43,384
Take the little yellow and green and,

69
00:03:43,383 --> 00:03:45,748
little touch of red here,

70
00:03:45,748 --> 00:03:48,122
and we just push some little
highlights coming down here.

71
00:03:48,122 --> 00:03:52,289
We'll make these little foothills
way back in the distance.

72
00:03:57,955 --> 00:03:59,006
Okay.

73
00:03:59,006 --> 00:04:01,506
Let's put some back over here.

74
00:04:03,504 --> 00:04:04,504
There we go.

75
00:04:13,939 --> 00:04:17,514
Then we'll take a clean brush,
and just gently lift up,

76
00:04:17,514 --> 00:04:18,728
very very lightly,

77
00:04:18,728 --> 00:04:21,755
just enough to give it an upward swirl.

78
00:04:21,755 --> 00:04:22,588
There.

79
00:04:27,149 --> 00:04:31,259
Very light, barely barely
touching the canvas.

80
00:04:31,259 --> 00:04:34,858
You let two or three
hairs just about touch.

81
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:38,442
Just enough to move
the paint a little bit.

82
00:04:39,898 --> 00:04:40,731
Okay.

83
00:04:41,576 --> 00:04:43,201
Now we'll take a little yellow

84
00:04:43,201 --> 00:04:46,300
and a little permanent
red mixed together here,

85
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:48,413
and we'll start putting
in some reflections.

86
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:50,533
Maybe we'll have a little,

87
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:55,487
have a little lake right
back here, a little pond.

88
00:04:55,487 --> 00:04:57,414
Just lay a little color on.

89
00:04:57,413 --> 00:04:58,997
And pull this down.

90
00:05:02,985 --> 00:05:03,985
There we go.

91
00:05:09,788 --> 00:05:12,757
Then just enough to give
a little watery effect.

92
00:05:12,757 --> 00:05:14,104
Just

93
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,342
ripple it a little.

94
00:05:15,341 --> 00:05:17,425
We don't want to destroy.

95
00:05:18,927 --> 00:05:21,677
(water sloshing)

96
00:05:24,728 --> 00:05:26,012
Mm 'kay.

97
00:05:26,012 --> 00:05:27,951
(brush rattling)

98
00:05:27,951 --> 00:05:32,117
Clean the old brushes here,
and we'll move right along.

99
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:38,726
Okay now I'm gonna go back
into this brown and Alizarin.

100
00:05:38,726 --> 00:05:41,262
Once again we're mixing it on the brush.

101
00:05:41,262 --> 00:05:43,698
A lot of paint on the brush.

102
00:05:43,699 --> 00:05:47,985
Maybe we'll put a little
tree standing back here.

103
00:05:47,985 --> 00:05:51,235
We'll make this one with the fan brush.

104
00:05:56,242 --> 00:05:57,242
There we go.

