00:08:49,576 --> 00:08:51,356
And they work very very well.

145
00:08:51,356 --> 00:08:55,451
They're very strong, very simple to build.

146
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:56,283
Okay.

147
00:08:56,283 --> 00:08:59,004
We've got that filled in.

148
00:08:59,004 --> 00:09:02,375
Let's put some tree trunks here and there.

149
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,993
Okay.

150
00:09:03,993 --> 00:09:07,910
And we'll put some dark
paint right along here.

151
00:09:09,798 --> 00:09:10,798
There we go.

152
00:09:14,562 --> 00:09:15,715
Just, in your mind,

153
00:09:15,715 --> 00:09:17,533
wherever you visualize there
might be a little trunk,

154
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:18,951
just drop one in.

155
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:24,288
Now mix just a little brown and white,

156
00:09:24,288 --> 00:09:26,385
so we can put a little
touch of highlight on this

157
00:09:26,385 --> 00:09:28,968
and make it stand out a little,

158
00:09:32,232 --> 00:09:36,399
like a light's playing
through here and touching it.

159
00:09:36,399 --> 00:09:37,231
There.

160
00:09:42,219 --> 00:09:45,177
And we'll put a trunk right
over in this one, too.

161
00:09:45,177 --> 00:09:46,345
Little dabble.

162
00:09:53,028 --> 00:09:53,861
Okay.

163
00:09:54,870 --> 00:09:58,033
Now, if the sun's here, light's
coming from this direction,

164
00:09:58,033 --> 00:10:01,700
this would be highlighted
on the other side.

165
00:10:06,784 --> 00:10:10,760
Now probably in reality,
if the sky was this dark,

166
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:13,822
you would have nothing but silhouettes.

167
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:15,099
But that would be a boring picture.

168
00:10:15,099 --> 00:10:17,016
This is a lot more fun.

169
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:26,034
Okay, you take a little
bit of magic white,

170
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:27,698
little yellow,

171
00:10:27,698 --> 00:10:30,281
maybe a touch of Phthalo green.

172
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:37,964
And we can put some nice little leaves

173
00:10:37,964 --> 00:10:40,266
on all these little bushes.

174
00:10:40,265 --> 00:10:41,807
Look how that color stands out

175
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:43,698
against this black background.

176
00:10:43,698 --> 00:10:45,781
It just jumps out at you.

177
00:10:51,032 --> 00:10:52,449
Okay, now, let's,

178
00:10:54,105 --> 00:10:57,023
let's put some on this little bush.

179
00:11:01,845 --> 00:11:06,012
And there's some little
things growing down in here.

180
00:11:07,556 --> 00:11:10,423
Use your imagination, let it go.

181
00:11:10,423 --> 00:11:11,255
Let it go.

182
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:15,611
Remember, this is your world.

183
00:11:15,611 --> 00:11:19,778
In your world you can create
anything that you desire.

184
00:11:22,653 --> 00:11:25,820
Okay, let's do this old big tree here.

185
00:11:34,634 --> 00:11:37,442
What's so very nice about
these black canvases,

186
00:11:37,442 --> 00:11:39,073
if there's a light
shining directly on them

187
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:42,629
they look totally different
than if they're without a light.

188
00:11:42,629 --> 00:11:43,996
So in essence it's almost like

189
00:11:43,996 --> 00:11:46,459
having two paintings in one.

190
00:11:46,460 --> 00:11:49,345
Especially if you hang these,
after they're finished,

191
00:11:49,345 --> 00:11:51,630
over a light, so at night
if you turn the light on

192
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:53,774
it shines up on this,

193
00:11:53,774 --> 00:11:56,192
it's remarkable what happens.

194
00:12:01,687 --> 00:12:02,687
There we go.

